# Cursor Rules — g-sheet-mcp

This is a read-only Google Sheets MCP server using FastMCP + Google Sheets API v4 + ADC.

## Stack
- Python 3.11, uv, FastMCP (mcp[cli]>=1.9.0), google-api-python-client, pydantic v2

## Key files
- src/g_sheet_mcp/auth.py    — ADC loading + auto-auth flow
- src/g_sheet_mcp/sheets.py  — SheetsClient (all API calls here)
- src/g_sheet_mcp/models.py  — Pydantic response models
- src/g_sheet_mcp/server.py  — FastMCP server, 8 tools

## Rules
- Always use `from __future__ import annotations`
- Run scripts with `uv run`, install with `uv sync`
- Never hardcode credentials; always use ADC
- All public methods need docstrings
- Input validation: raise ValueError for empty strings, out-of-range ints
- Sheet names with spaces must be wrapped with _quote_sheet() in range notation
- Tests live in tests/; run with `uv run pytest`
- Integration tests: `INTEGRATION=1 uv run pytest tests/test_integration.py`

## MCP tools (8)
get_spreadsheet_info, list_sheets, read_range, read_sheet, read_sheet_as_records,
get_cell, find_in_spreadsheet, batch_read_ranges

## Auth
gcloud auth login --enable-gdrive-access --update-adc
→ ~/.config/gcloud/application_default_credentials.json
